      "description": "Available is a well-sorted 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) featuring the 3.6L M96 flat-six powerplant paired with a Getrag G96 6-speed manual transaxle. This example remains mechanically robust with a recently documented IMS bearing retrofit and rear main seal replacement. The chassis retains its factory-spec McPherson strut front and multi-link rear suspension geometry, providing precise turn-in and high-speed stability. Braking is handled by four-piston monobloc calipers over cross-drilled rotors, showing plenty of pad life. While the exterior displays minor road-wear consistent with its 'good' status, the drivetrain remains tight with linear power delivery across the rev range. An ideal driver-spec 911 for the purist.",
